text: Gösta Törner Gösta Törner (October 27, 1912, Stockholm - November 11, 1982, Stockholm) was a Swedish jazz trumpeter and bandleader. He was one of the first musicians to play hot jazz in Sweden, and worked extensively both as a session musician on recordings and with his own groups on Swedish national radio from the 1940s to the 1960s.
